In the very beginning of me
getting into the industry,

01:16:20.951 --> 01:16:24.453
I would, you know,
be out and about, and I would hear

01:16:24.538 --> 01:16:29.083
girls, or actresses,
or musicians, or whatever,

01:16:30.335 --> 01:16:33.212
you know, they would say, "Oh, no, I
don't want to be in a relationship

01:16:33.297 --> 01:16:35.590
"because I don't wanna
have to choose between

01:16:35.674 --> 01:16:38.092
"being in a relationship
and having a career."

01:16:38.176 --> 01:16:42.763
And I thought to myself,
"When I get to know that...

01:16:42.848 --> 01:16:45.474
"When I find that person,

01:16:45.559 --> 01:16:48.978
"that's gonna be my,
you know, life partner,

01:16:49.062 --> 01:16:50.646
"I won't ever have to choose.

01:16:50.731 --> 01:16:52.982
"Because they'll be accepting of me

01:16:53.066 --> 01:16:54.650
"completely, for who I am."

01:16:54.735 --> 01:16:57.570
Not...
Not me being able to just like

01:16:57.654 --> 01:16:59.864
do whatever I want, necessarily,

01:16:59.948 --> 01:17:05.995
but they won't be threatened
or have weird motives or whatever.

01:17:06.622 --> 01:17:08.873
They will be accepting of me,

01:17:08.957 --> 01:17:13.836
the things I love,
the ambition, what I aspire to be,

01:17:13.920 --> 01:17:16.756
what I want to create,
they'll be accepting and supportive.

01:17:16.840 --> 01:17:19.050
And then I
started to realize, "Oh, my God.

01:17:20.719 --> 01:17:22.511
"That's not true, that's...

01:17:22.596 --> 01:17:25.931
"Like, that fairy tale that I had
is not true for me right now."

01:17:26.725 --> 01:17:28.392
Yeah, but you still miss him.

01:17:28.560 --> 01:17:29.644
Yeah.

01:17:30.562 --> 01:17:32.396
I don't want to cry.

01:17:40.405 --> 01:17:45.868
Okay, again, everyone, this is a closed
rehearsal. A closed rehearsal.

01:17:46.912 --> 01:17:49.413
I'll tell you the truth, is that...

01:17:51.750 --> 01:17:54.126
I mean, I'm a romantic and I don't...

01:17:54.211 --> 01:17:56.420
I kinda believed in this fairy tale.

01:17:58.090 --> 01:17:59.215
I mean...

01:17:59.299 --> 01:18:02.635
And in some ways I think that's always
been to my advantage,

01:18:02.719 --> 01:18:05.680
because, like, if you can
believe in something great,

01:18:05.764 --> 01:18:07.682
I feel like you can
achieve something great.

01:18:09.267 --> 01:18:12.978
I have that same
belief system with everything.

01:18:13.271 --> 01:18:18.484
From career to my life,
my personal life, everything.

01:18:19.986 --> 01:18:23.364
And I will do
everything it takes to not fail.

01:18:23.448 --> 01:18:27.660
And I did
everything it took, but it still failed.

01:18:29.788 --> 01:18:33.165
The bad that
comes along with the good is a journey,

01:18:33.250 --> 01:18:35.292
and I learned so much
from that journey.

